HEADWORD: Ostic
<hw>Os"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From North American
Indian <ets>oshtegwon</ets> a head.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, or
applied to, the language of the Tuscaroras, Iroquois, Wyandots,
Winnebagoes, and a part of the Sioux Indians.</def>
<rj><au>Schoolcraft.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
